# Canonical cron schedule for companiesmarketcap. This is a *fragment*, not the
# whole crontab: the Hetzner VM's crontab (user `av`) is shared with other
# projects (e.g. foliotracker). Install/update it with scripts/install-cron.sh,
# which merges just this managed block in and leaves other entries untouched.
#
# Do NOT run `crontab scripts/crontab` directly — that would replace the entire
# crontab and delete the other projects' jobs.
#
# Times are UTC (Ubuntu cron ignores CRON_TZ). $HOME is expanded by /bin/sh when
# cron runs the command.
# >>> companiesmarketcap (managed by scripts/install-cron.sh) >>>
# Daily FMP data refresh at 23:00 UTC.
0 23 * * * $HOME/companiesmarketcap/scripts/refresh.sh >> $HOME/companiesmarketcap/scripts/refresh.log 2>&1
# <<< companiesmarketcap (managed by scripts/install-cron.sh) <<<
